What was produced in the Zuschlag & Associates Invoice Factory?
Soon, on October 8, the hearing of the criminal trial against János Zuschlag and members will be discussed.
The political man and his associates are accused of repeated commercial fraud committed within the framework of a criminal association that has caused considerable damage, and of other crimes, including forgery of documents.
According to the Public Prosecutor's Office, the money obtained from invitations to tender was used by them for private purposes, and they have often certified the carrying out of the activities through false invoices.
The state and municipal money, a total of 65 million florins, ended up partly in the coffers of the Fiatal Baloldal organization, partly in the pockets of some people.
According to the method, which was announced by the investigating authorities, they took the money obtained from invitations to tender on the basis of invoices for non-existent transactions and the associations never fulfilled their obligations.
