Today in Paris the European Summit for Equal Opportunities, organized this year by France having the rotating presidency of the European Union, began.
Lívia Járóka, MEP Fidesz of the European People's Party in her message addressed to the plenum as the main speaker of the congress, drew attention to school segregation because it is the most serious legal violation that affects Roma children and also the most serious obstacle to their affirmation.
Mr Xavier Bertrand, French Minister for Employment and Social Affairs, on behalf of the French Presidency, and Mr Vladimír Špidla, European Commissioner for Employment, Social Affairs and Equal Opportunities, opened the conference at the highest level.
